   Research Training

     __________________________________________________________________

   The Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ) provides
   predoctoral and postdoctoral health services research education support
   and career development through a variety of programs. Select
   Application Deadline Dates (select for text version, table version) for
   programs of interest.

   For technical assistance from staff proposed projects, select Staff
   Contacts.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Programs

   Career Development Grants in Patient Safety (ASCII)
   Research and training grants to reduce medical errors and improve
   patient safety.
   Health Services Research Dissertation Awards (R03)
   Dissertation grants for doctoral candidates.
   Independent Scientist Awards (KO2)
   Career development support for promising new investigators.
   Individual Postdoctoral Fellowship Awards (F32)
   Available to applicants who have completed their clinical or research
   doctoral degrees.
   Institutional Training Awards (T32)
   National Research Service Award (NRSA) grants to institutions for
   predoctoral and postdoctoral training.
   Institutional Training Innovation Incentive Awards (R25)
   Support for design and implementation of new models of health services
   research training.
   Kerr White Visiting Scholars Program
   Intramural opportunities for junior, mid-career level, and senior
   researchers.
   Mentored Clinical Scientist Development Awards (K08)
   Specialized health services research study support for outstanding
   clinicians.
   Opportunities for Minority Candidates and Institutions
   Fostering education and career development of minority health services
   researchers.
   Predoctoral Fellowship Awards For Minority Students (F31)
   Designed to enhance racial and ethnic diversity in the health services
   research sciences.
   Summer Intern Program
   Short-term summer internships for undergraduate and graduate-level
   students.

